  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "The most commonly used word in Malayalam, as in many languages, is typically a function word such as a preposition, conjunction, or pronoun. In Malayalam, words like \"\u0d05\u0d35\u0d7b\" (avan - he), \"\u0d05\u0d35\u0d7e\" (aval - she), \"\u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d7b\" (njaan - I), and \"\u0d08\" (ee - this) are frequently used. However, the exact frequency can vary based on context and the specific texts being analyzed. If you\u2019re looking for specific usage in literature, spoken language, or another context, let me know!",
